version.description:
Released in October 2010, Unicode 6.0 was the first version of the Unicode Standard to support emoji.

Some characters in prior versions of Unicode were retroactively updated to provide an emoji presentation. This release was the first to introduce new characters for the sole purpose of compatability with emojis being used in Japan.

apple_vendor_description: On Apple devices, the six-thirty clock emoji displays a distinct analog face with a polished, 3D appearance, showcasing a precise time with a subtle glossy sheen. The minute and hour hands are elegantly rendered with soft, rounded edges, clearly indicating the half-hour mark. This emoji is often used to communicate a specific meeting time or to represent a moment in the day with a touch of Apple's characteristic visual clarity and sophistication.
